ship held up at calcutta some 10 indian ship have been held up at calcutta port after four day of industri action by local seamen , a spokesman for the shipown ' associ insa said . the disput ha prevent local crewmen sign on and off , but ha not affect foreign ship with intern crew dock at calcutta , which export tea and jute and import machineri , crude oil and petroleum product , the spokesman said . foreign ship may also suffer if dock worker join the action , he said . the ship corpor of india ( sci ) ha ask it ship to avoid the port until the disput is over , nation union of seafar in india presid leo barn said .